name: 17 Snacks That Are Perfect for Your Next Road Trip
Homemade Beef Jerky
ingredients: {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'smoked paprika, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'honey, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'freshly ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'beef top round, thinly sliced'}
steps: Whisk together Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, smoked paprika, honey, black pepper, red pepper flakes, garlic powder, and onion powder in a large bowl. Add beef; mix until completely coated with marinade. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and marinate in the refrigerator, 3 hours to overnight.. Preheat the oven to 175 degrees F (80 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil and place a wire rack on top.. Transfer beef to paper towels to dry. Discard marinade.. Arrange beef slices in a single layer on the prepared wire rack on the baking sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven until dry and leathery, 3 to 4 hours.. Cut jerky with scissors into bite-sized pieces.. Enjoy!

name: Cheese Crisps
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.. Shred generous amounts cheese.. Arrange cheese in 24 small heaps on the prepared baking sheets.. Bake in the preheated oven until golden brown, about 7 minutes. Cool for 5 to 10 minutes before removing from baking sheets.

name: Jerky Lover's Jerky - Sweet, Hot and Spicy!
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'cracked black pepper, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'lean beef sirloin tip, sliced into 1/8 inch strips'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pineapple juice'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'balsamic vinegar'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'teriyaki sauce'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'liquid smoke flavoring'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes, or to taste (Optional)'}
steps: Gather the ingredients.. Mix together onion powder, garlic powder, and black pepper in a small bowl or cup. Season beef lightly, using only part of the spice blend and reserving the rest. Place beef into an airtight plastic container or bowl, and refrigerate.. Stir together brown sugar, soy sauce, pineapple juice, balsamic vinegar, teriyaki sauce, Worcestershire sauce, and liquid smoke flavoring. Heat until brown sugar has completely dissolved. Refrigerate marinade until cool.. Pour cooled marinade over the seasoned meat, and mix by hand to coat. Seal the bowl, and refrigerate for at least 3 hours.. Arrange beef strips on the rack of a dehydrator, and sprinkle with a little bit more of the spice mixture and red pepper flakes. Dry for 5 hours, or to your desired dryness.

name: Spinach Balls
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'finely crushed herb-seasoned dry bread stuffing mix'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) package', 'name': 'frozen chopped spinach, thawed and drained'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'melted butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Combine stuffing mix, spinach, eggs, Parmesan cheese, melted butter, garlic powder, Italian seasoning, and black pepper in a large bowl; mix well. Use your hands to shape spinach mixture into walnut-sized balls and place on a baking sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven until heated through and browned, about 20 minutes.

name: Taco in a Bag
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'lean ground beef'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 ounce) package', 'name': 'taco seasoning mix'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '(2.5 ounce) packages', 'name': 'corn chips'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded lettuce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'chopped fresh tomato'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'salsa'}
steps: Cook and stir ground beef in a large skillet over medium heat until browned and crumbly, 7 to 10 minutes. Drain excess oil. Mix in water and taco seasoning. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.. Gently crush corn chips in the sealed bags. Snip one top and one bottom corner off each bag, then cut open along the side edge. Spoon equal amounts of beef, lettuce, Cheddar, tomato, sour cream, and salsa into each bag on top of crushed chips. Serve in the bag and eat using a fork.

name: Tortilla Rollups
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chunky salsa'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 ounce) package', 'name': 'dry fiesta-style ranch dressing mix'}, {'quantity': '10', 'unit': '(10 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}
steps: Stir together Cheddar cheese, salsa, sour cream, cream cheese, and ranch dressing mix in a medium bowl until combined. Spread evenly onto tortillas. Roll up tortillas and chill in the refrigerator until ready to serve.. To serve, cut rolled tortillas into 3/4-inch slices and arrange on a large serving platter.

name: High-Fiber, High-Protein Breakfast Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'quick-cooking oats'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'wheat germ'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ground flax seed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vanilla-flavored hemp protein powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'bananas'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'peanut butter (such as Jif®)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'natural peanut butter, or to taste'}
steps: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Line an 8x8-inch baking dish with aluminum foil, letting foil hang down over the sides of the pan; spray pan with cooking spray.. Stir oats, wheat germ, flax seed, protein powder, cinnamon, and salt together in a bowl. Mash bananas in a separate large bowl and stir 1/4 cup Jif® peanut butter, honey, and vanilla extract into bananas, mixing well. Stir dry ingredients into banana mixture and spread into the prepared baking dish.. Bake in the preheated oven for 20 minutes. Spread 1/4 cup natural peanut butter over top.. Continue baking until lightly browned on the edges and set, 10 more minutes. Let cool in the pan and lift bars onto a work surface using aluminum foil as handles. Cut into bars, wrap in plastic wrap, and store in refrigerator.

name: Avocado Toast (Vegan)
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'whole-grain bread'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'avocado, halved and pitted'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lemon, juiced, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}
steps: Toast bread in a toaster or toaster oven.. Mash avocado, parsley, olive oil, lemon juice, salt, black pepper, onion powder, and garlic powder together in bowl using a potato masher; spread on top of toast slices.

name: Wiener Winks
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) package', 'name': 'beef frankfurters'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'processed American cheese'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bread'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'butter'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Take 1 slice of bread and spread 1 teaspoon of butter on one side. Turn the bread over and place a slice of cheese on the bread. Place a frankfurter diagonally on the cheese. Fold bread corner to corner around the frankfurter. Insert a toothpick to hold together. Repeat steps for the remaining frankfurters.. Bake in a preheated oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

name: No Bake Granola Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '1 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chunky natural peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ground flaxseed'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried cranberries'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chocolate chips'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sliced almonds'}
steps: Stir oats, peanut butter, flaxseed, honey, cranberries, chocolate chips, and almonds together in a bowl; press into a 9x11-inch baking dish, using the back of a spatula to press into a flat layer.. Refrigerate mixture at least 1 hour.. Cut into 12 bars and wrap each individually in plastic wrap for storage.

name: Blueberry Oatmeal Breakfast Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole oats'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'oat flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'almond milk'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'melted butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh blueberries'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped walnuts'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded coconut (Optional)'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease an 8-inch square pan.. Combine whole oats, oat flour, brown sugar, salt, and baking soda in a bowl. Stir in almond milk, eggs, butter, and vanilla until well combined. Fold in blueberries and walnuts. Spread mixture into the prepared pan; top with shredded coconut.. Bake in the preheated oven until edges are golden and coconut is browned; about 35 minutes. Cool in the pan for 10 minutes before cutting into 16 squares.

name: Energy Balls
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'old-fashioned oats'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ground flax seed'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chocolate chips'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chia seeds (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Combine oats, peanut butter, ground flaxseed, chocolate chips, honey, chia seeds, and vanilla extract together in a bowl. Cover and chill the dough in the refrigerator for 30 minutes.. Remove chilled dough from the refrigerator; roll into twenty 1-inch diameter balls.

name: Air Fryer Oven Beef Jerky
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'London broil, thinly sliced and fat removed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'jerky seasoning'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'cure'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'cure'}
steps: Place beef, jerky seasoning, and 2 tablespoons plus 2 teaspoons cure in a large bowl. Massage beef with your hands until evenly combined. Cover and refrigerate, 8 hours to overnight.. Preheat the air fryer to 160 degrees F (70 degrees C). Place beef slices on the rack, making sure none are overlapping.. Air fry for 3 hours. Open the air fryer and let beef sit for 1 hour for final drying and cooling. Store in an airtight container.

name: Spinach Brownies
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) package', 'name': 'spinach, rinsed and chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'shredded mozzarella cheese'}
steps: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Lightly grease a 9x13 inch baking dish.. Place spinach in a medium saucepan with enough water to cover. Bring to a boil. Lower heat to simmer and cook until spinach is limp, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat, drain, and set aside.. In a large bowl, mix flour, salt and baking powder. Stir in eggs, milk and butter. Mix in spinach, onion and mozzarella cheese.. Transfer the mixture to the prepared baking dish. Bake in the preheated oven 30 to 35 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Cool before serving.

name: Easy Peanut Butter Energy Balls
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'crushed walnuts'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'semisweet chocolate chips'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey, or more as needed'}
steps: Combine oats, peanut butter, crushed walnuts, chocolate chips, and honey in the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment; beat until well combined, adding more honey if the mixture is not holding together.. Form 24 balls with a cookie scoop and place on a cookie sheet. Refrigerate until firm, 30 to 60 minutes.

name: Strawberry Oatmeal Breakfast Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'fresh strawberries'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lemon, juiced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'cornstarch'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'old-fashioned rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole wheat flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'packed light brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground ginger'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter, melted'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Butter a 9x12-inch baking dish.. Remove the green tops from strawberries using the tip of small, sharp knife or strawberry huller. Place the berries cut-side down on a work surface and cut in half. Slice each half lengthwise 3 to 5 times before turning and cutting across in a nice, uniform dice.. Combine diced strawberries, lemon juice, sugar, and cornstarch in a mixing bowl and stir until thoroughly combined and the cornstarch disappears. Set aside until needed.. Combine oats, all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, brown sugar, salt, and ginger in a mixing bowl. Pour in melted butter and stir thoroughly until dry ingredients are evenly coated.. Transfer 60% of the oatmeal mixture into the prepared baking dish and spread out into an even layer. Press the mixture down with the back of a spoon or spatula to compress slightly.. Place strawberries over the top using a slotted spoon. Do not press down. Reserve any accumulated juices in the bowl. Top with remaining oatmeal mixture and press down lightly with the back of a spoon or spatula. Drizzle reserved juices on top.. Bake in the preheated oven until the top is golden brown, about 45 minutes. Press the top down with a spatula to compress slightly. Let cool completely, about 1 hour. Cut into bars and serve.

name: High-Protein Energy Bites
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dark chocolate chips'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ground flax seeds'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chocolate-flavored protein powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsweetened shredded coconut'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chia seeds'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'coconut extract'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped coffee beans'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': "cocoa powder (such as Fry's®), or more as needed"}
steps: Mix oats, peanut butter, honey, dark chocolate chips, flax seeds, protein powder, coconut, chia seeds, and coconut extract together in a large bowl; fold in coffee beans. Form mixture into 1-inch balls.. Place cocoa powder in a small bowl. Roll each ball in the cocoa powder until coated.

name: Swedish Chocolate Balls (Chokladbollar)
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'quick-cooking rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '3 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'cocoa powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'coconut oil, at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'strong brewed coffee'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsweetened grated coconut, or as needed'}
steps: Heat a pan over medium heat and add oats. Toss and shake until fragrant and lightly toasted, 5 to 7 minutes.. Combine sugar, cocoa powder, salt, cayenne, butter, coconut oil, vanilla extract, and coffee in a bowl. Add the oats and mix until thoroughly combined.. Portion dough into balls using a sorbet scoop. Roll balls in grated coconut and transfer to a parchment-lined baking pan. Let them firm up in the fridge for 15 to 20 minutes.

name: Cheese Straws
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground red pepper (Optional)'}
steps: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Grease a cookie sheet.. In a large bowl cream butter and cheese. Stir in flour and salt; mix well. On a lightly floured surface, roll the dough out to 1/2 inch in thickness. Cut into 2 inch strips and sprinkle with ground red pepper. Place strips on prepared cookie sheet(s) 1 1/2 inches apart.. Bake in preheated oven for 10 to 15 minutes, or until crisp.

name: Oatmeal Energy Balls
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'natural peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'raisins'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}
steps: Combine oats, peanut butter, raisins, and honey with a fork in a bowl, then knead by hand until fully incorporated. Roll into 1-inch balls. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

name: Chef John's Chocolate Energy Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'pitted Medjool dates, roughly chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'raw cashews'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'raw or roasted unsalted almonds'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'high-quality unsweetened cocoa powder (such as Guittard Cocoa Rouge)'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsweetened shredded coconut'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'coconut oil, melted'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'cold espresso, or more as needed (or water)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}
steps: Place dates, cashews, almonds, cocoa powder, shredded coconut, coconut oil, cold espresso, vanilla, salt, and cayenne in the bowl of a food processor. Pulse on and off to start, then process for about 1 minute. Check to ensure mixture is sticky and moist enough to come together. Add more coffee if needed. Continue to process until mixture becomes a chunky mass.. Line a baking pan with plastic wrap. Scoop mixture into pan. Press down with a spatula until mixture is even. Place a layer of plastic wrap on the surface and smooth again with your hands. Refrigerate until cold and firm, 2 to 3 hours.. Remove from the pan and unwrap. Cut into 12 bars.

name: Soy Eggs (Shoyu Tamago)
ingredients: {'quantity': '10', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white vinegar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'reduced-sodium soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'prepared ponzu sauce'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mirin (Japanese sweet wine)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped scallions'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'roasted garlic'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'light brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'togarashi (Japanese red pepper condiment)'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'grated fresh ginger'}
steps: Place eggs in a pot. Cover with about 1 inch water. Remove eggs and stir vinegar into water. Bring to a boil. Gently place eggs back in the pot. Cover and cook for 5 minutes to soft-boil. Cook 3 minutes more for hard-boiled eggs. Prepare an ice bath in the meantime.. Remove heat and immediately place eggs in the ice bath. Peel eggs carefully.. Combine soy sauce, ponzu sauce, mirin, scallions, garlic, brown sugar, sesame oil, togarashi, and ginger in a container such as a jar. Mix well to ensure sugar dissolves and garlic breaks up.. Place eggs in mixture and seal. Marinate for 1 day. Eggs keep for 3 or 4 days after.

name: Bacon Popcorn
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'bacon grease'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unpopped popcorn kernels'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'seasoned salt, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'bacon bits (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese (Optional)'}
steps: Place bacon grease into a 6-quart pot and place over high heat. Add one or two popcorn kernels as testers. When test kernels pop, add remaining popcorn kernels and cover with a lid. As kernels start to pop, shake the pan back and forth constantly to keep unpopped kernels on the bottom. When popping slows down, remove the pan from heat and let it finish popping.. Pour popcorn into a large bowl or paper sack. Season with 1/2 of the seasoned salt and stir. Taste before adding more salt if desired. Toss with bacon bits and shredded Cheddar cheese for an extra special treat. Store leftovers in lunch sacks or sandwich bags.

name: Apricot Leather
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'pitted and diced fresh apricots'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 150 degrees F (165 degrees C), or the lowest setting you have.. Combine lemon juice, apricots, and sugar in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat until sugar has dissolved. Transfer to a blender and puree until smooth.. Cover an 11x17-inch pan or cookie sheet with a layer of plastic wrap. Pour pureed fruit onto the prepared pan and spread evenly to within 1 inch of the edge.. Bake for 4 to 6 hours in the preheated oven, using a spoon or a pair of tongs to keep the door slightly ajar, or until puree has dried and is no longer sticky. Once dry, you can cut it into strips; store in an airtight container.

name: Oat-Free and Gluten-Free Granola Bars (Clean Eating)
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'almonds, divided'}, {'quantity': '1 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'sunflower seeds, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded unsweetened coconut'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced dried apricots'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'coconut oil'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ground cinnamon, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}
steps: Place 3/4 cups almonds and 3/4 cups sunflower seeds into a food processor; chop until nuts are in 1/4-inch pieces, 1 to 2 minutes. Remove from food processor and pour in a bowl. Place remaining almonds and sunflower seeds into the food processor; roughly chop into larger pieces, about 1 minute. Mix remaining nuts, seeds, shredded coconut, and dried apricot into the 1/4-inch nuts until fruit-and-nut mixture is combined.. Combine coconut oil, honey, ground cinnamon, vanilla extract, and salt in a saucepan over medium-low heat; cook until the coconut oil mixture bubbles and turns a lighter color, 3 to 5 minutes.. Pour coconut oil mixture over fruit and nut mixture; stir until granola mixture takes on the consistency of wet sand, about 1 minute.. Line a baking sheet with waxed paper. Pour granola mixture onto sheet; place a second sheet of waxed paper on top of granola mixture. Push down on the waxed paper with your hands until granola mixture has been evenly spread. Pack very tightly so bars will not fall apart.. Let cool until granola has hardened, 2 to 3 hours. Cut into bars.

name: Greek Yogurt Peanut Butter Bites
ingredients: {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'natural peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'nonfat vanilla Greek yogurt'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'almond flour'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'flaxseed meal'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'cacao nibs'}
steps: Combine peanut butter, Greek yogurt, and honey in a medium bowl. Stir with a spoon until smooth. Add oats, almond flour, flaxseed meal, and cacao nibs. Stir until well incorporated.. Scoop up about 1 tablespoon of mixture with a small cookie scoop or spoon and roll lightly into a ball with your hands. Place in an airtight container and refrigerate for about 1 hour before serving.

name: Cranberry Nut Oatmeal Granola Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'quick-cooking oats'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried cranberries'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pecan halves'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ground flax seed'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk chocolate chips'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'wheat germ'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'packed light brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line an 8-inch square baking dish with parchment paper or waxed paper.. Mix oats, cranberries, pecans, ground flax seed, chocolate chips, and wheat germ together in a bowl.. Stir brown sugar, honey, vegetable oil, and salt together in a large microwave-safe bowl; heat in microwave for 30 seconds. Stir mixture and heat in microwave again until smooth, about 30 seconds more. Stir vanilla extract and cinnamon into brown sugar mixture.. Stir brown sugar mixture into oats mixture until evenly mixed and chocolate is melted; pour into the prepared baking dish.. Bake in the preheated oven until edges are golden brown, about 30 minutes. Lift bars out of pan by pulling by the parchment paper; cool for 5 minutes before cutting into bars.

name: Chewy No-Bake Granola Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'steel-cut oats'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'crispy rice cereal'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped mixed dried fruit'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped almonds'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mini chocolate chips'}
steps: Grease a 9x13-inch baking dish.. Mix rolled oats, steel-cut oats, rice cereal, dried fruit, and almonds together in a large bowl.. Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat; add brown sugar, honey, and vanilla. Whisk until sugar is completely dissolved, about 2 minutes. Pour over oat mixture; stir to combine.. Spread oat mixture into the prepared baking dish. Press chocolate chips into the top. Refrigerate until chilled, about 1 hour.. Sliced chilled granola mixture into 24 bars.

name: Easy Energy Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'miniature semisweet chocolate chips'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ground flax meal'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}
steps: Stir oats, chocolate chips, flax meal, peanut butter, honey, vanilla extract, and salt together in a bowl. Roll into 24 balls and refrigerate until firm, at least 30 minutes.

name: Banana Oat Energy Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'bananas, mashed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'carrots, grated'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'apple, grated'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsweetened applesauce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped peanuts'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 9x13-inch baking dish.. Mix oats, bananas, carrots, apple, applesauce, and peanuts together in a bowl; spread into the prepared baking dish.. Bake in the preheated oven until golden brown, about 20 minutes.

name: Oat Applesauce Muffins
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'buttermilk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole wheat flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'applesauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}
steps: Place oats in a small bowl, pour in buttermilk. Let sit for two hours at room temperature.. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Grease 12 muffin cups or line with paper muffin liners.. In a large bowl, stir together whole wheat flour, baking powder, baking soda and brown sugar. Stir in oat/buttermilk mixture, applesauce and egg; mix well. Pour batter into prepared muffin cups.. Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes, until a toothpick inserted into center of muffin comes out clean.

name: No Bake Energy Balls
ingredients: {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cocoa powder'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded coconut'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'wheat germ'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}
steps: Mix oats, peanut butter, honey, cocoa powder, coconut, wheat germ, vanilla extract, and cinnamon together in a bowl. Roll oat mixture into ping pong-sized balls. Place in a container and store in refrigerator.

name: Bird Seed Energy Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'old-fashioned rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar, packed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'wheat germ'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'whole wheat flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'canola oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'flax seeds'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sesame seeds'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sunflower seeds'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'semi-sweet chocolate chips'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease a 9x14 inch ovenproof baking dish.. Mix the rolled oats, brown sugar, wheat germ, cinnamon, and flour together in a large bowl. In a separate bowl, whisk together the eggs, honey, canola oil, vanilla, and salt until evenly blended., and stir into the oat mixture. Stir in the flax seeds, sesame seeds, sunflower seeds, and chocolate chips. Use your hands to mix the ingredients, and press the mixture into the prepared pan.. Bake in preheated oven until the edges are golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes. Cool completely in the baking dish before cutting into 2 inch bars.

name: Best Beef Jerky
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'beef brisket'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'thick teriyaki sauce'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dark corn syrup (such as Karo®)'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'liquid smoke flavoring'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sesame seeds'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}
steps: Place beef brisket in the freezer for 1 hour to make slicing easier.. Place brisket on a flat work surface. Slice on the grain into the thinnest possible strips, about 1/4-inch-thick.. Place beef strips in the bottom of a large bowl or container. Pour in teriyaki sauce, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, corn syrup, liquid smoke, brown sugar, sesame seeds, garlic powder, honey, onion powder, and cayenne pepper. Mix well until beef is evenly coated and submerged. Cover with plastic wrap and marinate in the refrigerator for 24 hours.. Remove beef and pat dry using paper towels. Place beef in a single layer on the trays of a dehydrator machine. Cook at 155 degrees F (68 degrees C), or according to manufacturer's instructions, until dry and firm, yet slightly pliable, about 5 hours.. Leave beef out in the air to cool until dry; the longer you leave it out, the drier it will get.

name: Homemade Fig Newtons
ingredients: {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole wheat flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'finely ground walnuts'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'grated orange zest'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried figs'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'orange, juiced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'grated orange zest'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}
steps: Combine whole wheat flour, ground walnuts, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, and nutmeg in a medium bowl.. Beat butter, brown sugar, and honey together in a large bowl until light and fluffy. Add egg, orange zest, and vanilla extract; beat until thoroughly combined. Add flour mixture in 3 batches, mixing until just combined and dough is very soft and sticky.. Wrap dough in plastic wrap. Pat into a disk and refrigerate, 4 hours to overnight.. Place figs, water, honey, orange juice, vanilla extract, orange zest, and nutmeg in a medium saucepan. Bring filling mixture to a simmer over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Cook until figs are softened and fall apart easily when pressed with a spoon, about 15 minutes. Remove from heat and cool for 10 minutes.. Place filling mixture into a blender or food processor and puree until smooth. Pour puree into a glass container and let cool completely until filling has a spreadable consistency. Refrigerate until ready to use.. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Place a piece of parchment paper on a work surface and generously flour the paper and a rolling pin. Roll out the chilled cookie dough into a 10x14-inch rectangle about 1/4 inch thick. Continue to flour the parchment and rolling pin as necessary. Divide dough into 4 strips about 3 1/2 inches wide by 10 inches long.. Divide the fig filling among the strips of dough. Spread filling lengthwise down the center of each piece, leaving about 1/2 inch of space on the sides. Gently pull one side of the dough halfway over the filling. Repeat with the opposite side and pinch to seal in the filling to form a cookie log about 1 inch wide and 10 inches long.. Gently roll the log over so it's seam-side down. Brush off any excess flour and gently press the top of the roll to flatten slightly. Repeat this process with the other dough strips.. Brush off any excess flour from the top of, and in between, the cookie logs. Gently lift the parchment paper, with the cookies still on it, onto a baking sheet. Arrange logs about 1 inch apart on the baking sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven until cookies just begin to brown and feel slightly crispy to the touch, 20 to 25 minutes. Let cookies cool for 5 minutes. Use a serrated knife to slice each log into 8 pieces about 1 1/4 inch long and 1 inch wide. Let cookies cool completely, at least 40 minutes.. Store cooled cookies in an airtight container until softened, 8 hours to overnight.

name: Homemade Energy Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '3 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sweetened dried cranberries (such as Craisins)'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sunflower seeds'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white chocolate chips'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'toasted sesame seeds'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'oat bran'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'flax seeds'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'creamy natural peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Mix oats, cranberries, sunflower seeds, chocolate chips, sesame seeds, oat bran, flax seeds, cinnamon, and salt together in a large bowl. Stir in peanut butter, honey, and oil until well combined. Press mixture firmly into a 9x13-inch baking pan.. Bake in the preheated oven until golden, 12 to 15 minutes. Remove from the oven and let cool for 5 minutes. Transfer to the refrigerator and chill for 10 minutes to set.. Slice chilled bars into twenty 2x3-inch squares. Wrap each bar in plastic wrap and store in the refrigerator.

name: Peanut Butter Energy Balls
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'toasted wheat germ'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'nonfat dry milk powder'}
steps: Combine wheat germ, peanut butter, honey, and milk powder in a bowl; shape into 20 bite-sized balls. Arrange balls on a plate.. Place in the freezer until solid, at least 1 hour.

name: Blueberry Banana Breakfast Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ⅓', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'coarsely chopped dried figs'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'coarsely chopped almonds'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sunflower seeds'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mashed ripe bananas'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'smooth peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'large egg whites'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh blueberries'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'flax seeds'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'sunflower seeds'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line an 8-inch square baking pan with parchment paper, leaving 1 inch of parchment hanging over the sides.. Mix oats, figs, almonds, and 1/4 cup sunflower seeds together in a bowl.. Stir bananas, peanut butter, and honey together in a saucepan over medium-low heat until completely melted and smooth, about 5 minutes. Remove saucepan from heat.. Whisk egg whites together in a bowl until foamy. Mix banana mixture into egg whites and whisk until smooth; add oat mixture and stir until batter well combined. Fold blueberries into batter. Press batter into the prepared pan; top with flax seeds and 1 tablespoon sunflower seeds.. Bake in the preheated oven until golden, about 30 minutes. Cool completely before cutting into bars.

name: Pogaca (Feta Dumplings)
ingredients: {'quantity': '3 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'canola oil'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'plain yogurt'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'beaten eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'crumbled feta cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'finely chopped fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg yolks'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sesame seeds'}
steps: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Mix the flour with baking soda in a bowl; set aside.. Mix the canola oil, butter, yogurt, eggs, sour cream, sugar, and salt together in a large mixing bowl until smooth. Gradually stir the flour mixture into the wet ingredients to form a soft dough. Knead and squeeze the dough in the bowl until it is no longer sticky, about 5 minutes. Stir the feta cheese, parsley, olive oil, and paprika together in a bowl with a fork to make a filling.. Make each dumpling by pinching off about 2 1/2 tablespoons of dough; roll into a ball about 1 3/4 inches across between your hands, and press it into a flat circle 3 inches across on your palm. Spoon 1 scant tablespoon of filling into the center of the circle. Bring the edges of the circle together over the filling, and pinch them together to make a fat, round little stuffed dumpling. Set the dumplings onto the parchment paper-lined baking sheet, seam sides down. Beat the egg yolks in a small bowl, and brush the pogaca tops with the egg yolk. Sprinkle each with about 1/4 teaspoon of sesame seeds.. Bake in the preheated oven until the tops are shiny, brown, and crackled, 20 to 30 minutes.

name: 5-Ingredient Keto and Vegan Chocolate Almond Balls
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'almond flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'almond butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegan chocolate chips'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped almonds'}
steps: Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. Combine almond flour, almond butter, and vanilla extract in a bowl; mix until well combined and a soft dough is formed. Shape dough into 1/2-inch balls and place on the prepared baking sheet. Freeze until set, about 20 minutes.. Melt chocolate chips in a microwave-safe glass or ceramic bowl in 15-second intervals, stirring after each interval, 1 to 3 minutes. Dip cookie balls in the melted chocolate and place on the prepared baking sheet. Sprinkle with chopped almonds and let sit until chocolate is set, about 10 minutes.

name: Peanut Butter Protein Balls
ingredients: {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'oats'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chocolate chips, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'scoops', 'name': 'protein powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}
steps: Combine milk, peanut butter, oats, chocolate chips, protein powder, and cinnamon in a medium mixing bowl and mix.. Scoop and shape into balls using a spoon. Place into a freezer bag and store in the freezer.

name: Kids' Snack
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) package', 'name': 'sweetened honey corn and oat cereal'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) package', 'name': 'bear-shaped graham cookies'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10.5 ounce) package', 'name': 'miniature marshmallows'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) package', 'name': 'semisweet chocolate chips'}
steps: Combine all ingredients in a large bag and shake to mix. Divide and store in individual baggies for a fast treat.

name: Sesame Date Rolls
ingredients: {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'chopped dried dates'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'hot water as needed'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'toasted sesame seeds, divided'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped walnuts'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole raw almonds'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsweetened shredded coconut'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'coconut oil'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cardamom'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}
steps: Place dates in a small bowl and completely cover with hot water. Allow to soak until softened, 10 to 15 minutes. Drain, and reserve soaking liquid.. Combine soaked dates, 2 tablespoons toasted sesame seeds, walnuts, almonds, coconut, coconut oil, cardamom, cinnamon, vanilla, and salt in the bowl of a large food processor. Pulse several times until mixture comes together to form a soft "dough," scraping down the sides of the bowl as needed. If mixture is too dry, add reserved soaking liquid, 1 tablespoon at a time, until desired consistency is reached.. Turn out dough on a piece of parchment paper. Roll into a 10-inch long by 1 1/2-inch wide log using lightly greased hands. Sprinkle remaining toasted sesame seeds evenly over log on all sides, pressing them in gently. Wrap log in parchment paper, and refrigerate until firm, at least 1 to 2 hours.. Remove log from fridge, and cut into about sixteen 1/2-inch thick rounds. Serve immediately or store in the refrigerator until ready to use.

name: Gluten-Free Fried Oatmeal Bites
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'almond milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'quick-cooking oats'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cane sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'Himalayan pink salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'gluten-free all purpose baking flour'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil, or as needed'}
steps: Bring water to a boil in a pot; reduce heat to low. Add almond milk and stir in oats. Add sugar, stirring vigorously. Stir in salt. Continue to simmer until oats have reached your desired consistency, 3 to 5 minutes. Remove from heat and let cool, 15 to 20 minutes.. Transfer oats to a lidded container, cover, and chill in a refrigerator, 30 minutes to 2 hours.. Whisk egg in a small bowl. Place gluten-free flour in a separate bowl.. Scoop chilled oatmeal into medium-size balls.. Heat oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.. Place oatmeal balls into egg wash until completely covered. Place in flour; cover entirely. Use a slotted spoon to remove floured oatmeal balls; shake off excess flour.. Place oatmeal balls into the hot oil and cook until golden brown, 3 to 4 minutes on each side.

name: Chocolate Chip Coconut No-Bake Granola Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'dates, pitted'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'unsweetened shredded coconut'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'miniature chocolate chips'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'whole raw almonds'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pumpkin seeds'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'salted sunflower seeds'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'almond butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsweetened applesauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}
steps: Line a 9x13-inch baking dish with waxed paper so that the paper hangs over the edges of dish.. Combine dates and water in a food processor or blender; process until a paste forms, adding more water if needed to thin it.. Combine oats, coconut, chocolate chips, almonds, pumpkin seeds, sunflower seeds, and cinnamon in a large bowl. Add date paste, almond butter, applesauce, and vanilla extract; mix, using your hands, until wet ingredients are fully incorporated.. Press mixture into the prepared baking dish. Cover with another piece of waxed paper and press down using a can or mini roller. Freeze for 1 hour.. Remove dish from freezer and lift out of dish using the edges of the waxed paper. Cut into 25 squares.

name: M&M's® Granola Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': "candy-coated milk chocolate pieces (such as M&M's®)"}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'flax seed meal'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Stir oats, milk chocolate pieces, flour, flax seed meal, brown sugar, and salt together in a large bowl. Make a well in the center of the oat mixture.. Whisk egg in a separate bowl until light and fluffy. Add honey, oil, and vanilla; whisk until well-combined. Pour egg mixture into the well in the oat mixture. Stir until evenly combined. Pour mixture into a 9x13-inch glass baking dish; pat down and spread the mixture flat, leaving at least 1-inch of space between the mixture and the sides of the dish.. Bake in the preheated oven until golden and set, about 25 minutes.

name: Crispy Cereal Mix

steps: Preheat oven to 250 degrees F (120 degrees C). Melt the margarine in a 9x13 inch baking pan.. Remove baking pan from oven. Stir in the Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, seasoning salt and onion powder. Gradually mix in the nuts, pretzels, bagel chips, crispy corn cereal squares, crispy rice cereal squares, and crispy wheat cereal squares. Evenly coat all ingredients.. Bake approximately 1 hour in the preheated oven. Drain on paper towels.

name: Perfect Apple Chips
ingredients: {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Granny Smith apple, sliced into 1/16-inch thick rounds'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red apple (such as Paula), sliced into 1/16-inch thick rounds'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'fleur de sel (sea salt) to taste'}
steps: Preheat oven to 170 degrees F (77 degrees C). Line two baking sheets with parchment paper and lightly oil the paper.. Stir lime juice, water, and sugar in a bowl until sugar is dissolved. Soak apple slices in lime juice mixture to combine flavors, 2 to 5 minutes. Drain and discard liquid.. Arrange apple slices in a single layer about 1/8-inch apart on prepared baking sheets. Sprinkle with Fleur de Sel.. Bake apples in the preheated oven until dried and crisp, about 4 hours. Cool completely before carefully peeling from the parchment.

name: Zucchini Chocolate Oatmeal Bites
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'gluten-free oats'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'almond butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'coarsely shredded zucchini'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dairy-free mini chocolate chips'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'flaxseed meal'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}
steps: Mix oats, almond butter, zucchini, chocolate chips, honey, flaxseed meal, and ground cinnamon in a large bowl until combined.. Divide mixture into 18 bite-sized pieces and roll into balls. Arrange in a storage container and refrigerate until set, about 1 hour.

name: Sweet and Spicy High-Protein Snack Mix
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'wheat cereal squares'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'toasted oat cereal'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'small pretzels'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'bite-sized cheese crackers'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted sunflower seeds'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'unsalted mixed nuts'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried cherries'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(1.5 ounce) packages', 'name': '100% smoked beef sticks, cut into bite-sized pieces'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 250 degrees F (120 degrees C).. Combine wheat cereal squares, oat cereal, pretzels, crackers, sunflower seeds, and nuts in a large bowl. Set aside.. Combine butter, honey, Worcestershire sauce, salt, cayenne pepper, chili powder, garlic powder, and onion powder in a small saucepan and over medium-low heat. Mix until butter is melted and spices are blended in smoothly. Pour seasoned butter over dry mixture and stir until well combined. Spread out onto a large baking sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Let cool completely.. Mix in dried cherries and smoked beef stick pieces.

name: Great Garlic Knots
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(11 ounce) container', 'name': 'refrigerated breadstick dough'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg, lightly beaten'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped fresh rosemary'}
steps: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).. Tie the dough into 12 knots and place them onto a cookie sheet. Brush the knots with the egg, and sprinkle the rosemary and garlic onto the knots. Bake the knots according to the package directions.

name: No-Bake Power Bites
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'almond butter'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsweetened shredded coconut'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chocolate chips'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cocoa nibs'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'sea salt to taste'}
steps: Mix almond butter, honey, and vanilla extract together in a bowl until smooth. Stir oats, coconut, chocolate chips, cocoa nibs, and sea salt into almond butter mixture until well combined; refrigerate for 30 minutes.. Roll mixture into balls using your hands.

name: Gingerbread Granola Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'old-fashioned rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cloves'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground ginger'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'molasses'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease two 9x13-inch baking sheets.. Mix oats, flour, brown sugar, white sugar, salt, cinnamon, cloves, and ginger in a large bowl. Stir in oil, honey, molasses, and eggs. Mix until well-combined. Pat mixture onto baking sheets using your hands.. Bake in the preheated oven until edges begin to brown and center no longer looks glossy, 15 to 20 minutes.. Cool for about 10 minutes; cut into bars while still warm.

name: Whey Protein Energy Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '15', 'unit': '', 'name': 'dates, pitted and chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'oat flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whey protein powder'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsweetened cocoa powder'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped pecans, divided'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded coconut, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'water, or more as needed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'semisweet chocolate chips'}
steps: Place dates in a bowl and add boiling water to cover. Let soak for 10 minutes. Strain dates and discard the water.. Blend oat flour, protein powder, and cocoa powder in a food processor until well combined. Add dates, 1/2 cup pecans, 1/2 cup coconut, vanilla, and salt. Pulse to combine, adding water as needed, to get a soft dough consistency.. Transfer dough to a bowl. Add remaining pecans, remaining coconut, and chocolate chips; mix well.. Scrape dough onto a piece of parchment paper and place another piece of parchment paper on top. Toll bars out to about 1/2-inch thick. Refrigerate until firm, 2 to 3 hours.. Slice into 12 bars and serve.

name: Chocolate-Cranberry Energy Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'raw almonds'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'walnuts'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pitted dates'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried cranberries'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded coconut'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'unsweetened cocoa powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. Pulse almonds and walnuts together in the bowl of a food processor until chopped. Add dates and cranberries, a little at a time, and continue to chop. Add coconut, cocoa, and vanilla extract. Process to desired consistency.. Roll dough into a 2-inch wide log and cut into ten 3/4-inch thick pucks. Place on the prepared baking sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven until set, about 10 minutes.

name: Chewy Oatmeal Coconut Bar Cookies
ingredients: {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'coconut oil'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'agave nectar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Melt brown sugar, coconut oil, and agave nectar in a small pot over medium heat; bring to a boil. Remove from heat; add oats and flour. Pour into an 8-inch baking dish.. Bake in the preheated oven until lightly browned, about 20 minutes. Refrigerate until solid, at least 20 minutes. Cut into squares; you may need to pick up the whole thing and cut it from the side.

name: Bright Day Banana Muffins
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'bananas'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg whites'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'canola oil'}, {'quantity': '1 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'whole wheat flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': '', 'name': 'paper muffin cup liners'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line 12 muffin cups with paper liners.. Mash bananas in a bowl until no lumps remain. Add brown sugar, egg whites, egg, and canola oil; mix thoroughly. Stir flour, oats, baking soda, salt, and baking powder into the batter until just combined.. Fill muffin cup 2/3-full with batter.. Bake in the preheated oven until tops spring back when lightly pressed, 20 to 25 minutes.

name: Fruit-Oat Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'packed brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'whole wheat flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unbleached all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground allspice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sliced fresh strawberries'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh blueberries'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Coat a 10x14-inch baking dish with cooking spray.. Combine brown sugar and butter in a large bowl; beat with an electric mixer until smooth and creamy.. Mix together whole wheat flour, all-purpose flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda, and allspice in a separate bowl. Gradually pour flour mixture into the butter mixture; blend well. Stir in oats and mix with a wooden spoon until incorporated. Press 1/2 of the oat batter firmly into the bottom of the prepared baking dish.. Bake in the preheated oven for 10 minutes. Spread strawberries and blueberries over the crust and sprinkle with remaining oat batter. Press slightly to flatten batter and fruit. Bake until edges are golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.. Remove from the oven and let cool completely in the pan. Cut into 24 bars.

name: Camp Trail Mix
ingredients: {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'honey-oat cereal'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'peanuts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried cranberries'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'carob chips'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sunflower seeds'}
steps: Combine the cereal, peanuts, cranberries, carob chips, and sunflower seeds in a mixing bowl. Store at room temperature in an airtight container.

name: Healthy After-School Granola Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'oats'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'quinoa'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'slivered almonds'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chia seeds'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'crunchy peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'coconut oil, warmed'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'flaxseed meal'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'dark chocolate chips'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Spread oats, quinoa, almonds, and chia seeds on a baking sheet.. Toast in the preheated oven, stirring halfway through, until golden brown, about 15 minutes.. Mix peanut butter, honey, and coconut oil together in a bowl until thoroughly combined. Mix in oat mixture, flaxseed meal, and salt until well combined. Press granola mixture into a 12x18-inch baking pan.. Bake in the preheated oven until bars set, about 5 minutes. Remove from oven; sprinkle with chocolate chips. Bake until chocolate is just melted, about 5 minutes. Spread melted chocolate evenly over bars with a rubber spatula.. Place in the freezer until chocolate is firm, about 20 minutes; cut into bars.

name: Peanut Butter Trail Mix Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'granola'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'whole bran cereal'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'instant nonfat dry milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried cranberries'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sunflower seeds'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'almonds'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'raisins'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ground flax seeds'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}
steps: Mix together granola, bran cereal, dry milk, cranberries, sunflower seeds, almonds, raisins, and flax seeds in a large bowl.. Add peanut butter-honey mixture to the dry ingredients and stir well to combine.. Press mixture into a 9x13-inch baking pan lined with parchment or waxed paper.. Refrigerate for 30 minutes before cutting into bars.

name: Applesauce Oatmeal Bites for Toddlers
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'quick-cooking oats'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'applesauce'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line an 8-inch square baking dish with parchment paper.. Combine oats and applesauce until moist. Spread into the prepared baking dish.. Bake in the preheated oven until sticky, 10 to 12 minutes.. Remove from the oven, flip onto a cutting board, and cut into 1-inch squares. Allow to cool before serving.

name: Cinnamon and Raisin Spread
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fat free cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cottage cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'raisins'}
steps: Place fat free cream cheese, cottage cheese, cinnamon and white sugar in a food processor. Blend until smooth. Transfer to a medium bowl. Stir in raisins. Cover and chill in the refrigerator until serving.

name: Fluffy Low-Fat Vegan Blueberry Muffins
ingredients: {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soy milk'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': '', 'name': 'dates, pitted'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'flax seeds'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'rolled oats, ground'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'brown sugar (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'applesauce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh blueberries'}
steps: Combine soy milk, water, dates, and flax seeds in a bowl.. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Combine ground oats, brown sugar, baking powder, and cinnamon in a large bowl.. Combine the date mixture, applesauce, and vanilla extract in a blender. Blend until evenly mixed; pour into the bowl with the oat mixture. Stir until no dry spots remain. Fold in blueberries. Pour batter into a 12-cup muffin tin.. Bake in the preheated oven until tops spring back when lightly pressed, about 20 minutes. Let cool in the tin.

name: Chocolate-Cherry-Coconut Granola Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '2 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'old-fashioned rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'puffed rice cereal'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsweetened coconut flakes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'slivered almonds'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried tart cherries'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'creamy peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'coconut oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mini semisweet chocolate chips'}
steps: Line a 9x13-inch baking pan with a piece of parchment paper that is large enough to go up all sides of the pan.. Combine oats, rice cereal, coconut, almonds, and cherries in a large mixing bowl and set aside.. Combine honey, peanut butter, brown sugar, coconut oil, vanilla extract, and salt in a small saucepan. Heat over medium heat until brown sugar is melted; continue to simmer for 1 minute more. Pour heated mixture into the dry ingredients and stir to fully combine. Stir in chocolate chips.. Pour granola into the prepared baking pan and press firmly with a nonstick spatula or lightly oiled hands to tightly compact and distribute evenly throughout.. Refrigerate for 2 hours.. Remove from the refrigerator and slice into 20 equal portions. Tightly wrap individually in plastic wrap or serve immediately.

name: Peanut Butter Monster Cookie Dream Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'melted butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'sweetened condensed milk'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': "candy-coated milk chocolate pieces (such as M&M's)"}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).. Stir oats, flour, butter, brown sugar, baking soda, and salt together in a bowl. Reserve 1 1/2 cups of crumb mixture. Spread remaining mixture into a 9x13-inch baking pan.. Bake in the preheated oven until crust is lightly browned, about 12 minutes. Remove crust; leave oven on.. Mix sweetened condensed milk and peanut butter together in a bowl. Spread over the baked crust. Sprinkle the reserved crumb mixture and milk chocolate pieces on top.. Bake in the preheated oven until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
